  "prompt": "What is the validity period of Non-Creamy OBC certificate?",
  "response": "The validity period of a Non-Creamy Layer OBC (Other Backward Classes) certificate can vary by state and institution in India, as there is no uniform, nationwide standard. Generally, the certificate is typically issued for a validity period of one year, but some states or institutions may have different policies.\n\nIt is advisable to check with the relevant state government authority or the institution requiring the certificate for precise details regarding validity and renewal processes.",
